1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,369
Yes, this is my car.

2
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:37,287
That's why I can't find it.

3
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,872
They're not going to theMoravianos first.

4
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:41,958
Mikoy is going home because
he wants to meet his mother and father.

5
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:06,066
Mikoy, where is Chiara?
Why is she still not here?

6
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:32,884
My child.

7
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,978
And so is Mikoy's.

8
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,287
Because I believe

9
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:05,291
that after all these sacrifices,

10
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,961
it will all be worth it at the end.

11
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,639
She really is looking for the bomb.

12
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:35,655
I'll match her.

13
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:38,575
That could be dangerous, Chiara.

14
00:02:51,379 --> 00:02:55,508
They may not be as wealthy
or as influential as the Concordat.

15
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:57,302
But believe me.

16
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:59,888
There are more good people

17
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:03,349
who are willing to fight
for what they believe is right.

18
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,592
Come on!

19
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:40,178
I brought something to keep us awake,
not to compete with it.

20
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,932
You know, maybe you should relax first.

21
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,560
I brought everything.

22
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,103
I didn't know what you preferred.

23
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:50,647
But if you want something else,
just tell me.

24
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,190
I'll get it from the kitchen.

25
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,486
I'll take the coffee.
You can have the tea.

26
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:57,987
Thanks.

27
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:08,957
You've been through so much,

28
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:12,377
trials, explosions,
and threats to your life,

29
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,545
yet you always have a joke ready.

30
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:16,130
Of course!

31
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,632
Right?

32
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:29,644
Why? It works, doesn't it?

33
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:31,062
You always laugh.

34
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:33,606
I think I deserve an award by now.

35
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:38,736
For making Special Agent
Alexandria Cortez smile.

36
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,405
That's a tough mission.

37
00:04:40,488 --> 00:04:41,739
A really tough one!

38
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,273
But first, I have to find the bomb.

39
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:18,026
I have to beat Isabella to it.

40
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,195
But seriously, Mikoy,

41
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,282
I think you need psychological support.

42
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:27,410
Just let us know,
and we can arrange that for you.

43
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:32,040
What happened at your house
and your cake bakery wasn't a small thing.

44
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:41,632
Thanks, Alex.

45
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:44,552
It's just…

46
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:46,429
right now,

47
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:55,229
You know,
I think my sibling was right about me.

48
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,690
He said whenever I have a problem,

49
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:02,195
my default response
is to act like everything's okay.

50
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,448
I don't know.

51
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,242
Maybe that's just how it is
when you're the eldest.

52
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:12,121
There's this unspoken rule
that you have to handle everything.

53
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,290
That you can't let anyone see
you're struggling.

54
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,835
But it's about time you unlearned that.

55
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:19,962
We're a team, remember?

56
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,423
So you can always confide in us.

57
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:27,595
My child.

58
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,026
She cannot be stopped.

59
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:45,613
If she wants to bring destruction,

60
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:48,366
she'll make sure it happens.

61
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:55,164
I'll be the one to stop her.

62
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,231
Thanks, Alex.

63
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,025
I owe you all so much.

64
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,488
Don't worry, I've kept track.

65
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:41,919
Hey!

66
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:43,629
It's hot!

67
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:44,547
Come on!

68
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:48,593
You just keep throwing those punchlines.

69
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:49,844
My bad.

70
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:03,149
Get some sleep, Papa.

71
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:23,794
By the way, why hasn't
Chiara come back yet?

72
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,297
I don't think she's coming back.

73
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:28,382
Huh?

74
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,342
Come on.

75
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:30,676
Of course she'll come back.

76
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,428
She's my sweetheart.

77
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:34,722
But what if she doesn't?

78
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:38,935
What if she went back to the Moravianos?

79
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:28,234
Easy! Come on.

80
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:29,902
- Brusko?
- Yep!

81
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:31,404
It's just me!

82
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:35,700
Rain or shine, Brusko at your service.

83
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:40,037
Chiara made a complete
180-degree turnaround.

84
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:44,542
But I won't blame her
if she reverts to what's familiar to her.

85
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:52,383
Come on, Agent Alex.

86
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:54,427
Have a little optimism.

87
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:58,055
Didn't you say we're all one team now?

88
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:03,686
So we might as well
trust each other more. Right?

89
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:11,527
How can I be sure
you're not working for La Morte Bianca?

90
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,154
Come on.

91
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,866
No matter the threats

92
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,702
or how much money La Morte Bianca has,

93
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:28,669
Besides, I have to play it smart,
so I look like a loyal soldier.

94
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:30,171
That way, she won't get suspicious.

95
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,549
Promise. Cross my heart and hope to die.

96
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:39,847
Mikoy, let me remind you.

97
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:43,601
You and Chiara escaped under our watch.

98
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:46,395
Do you know how much stress that caused us

99
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,315
just to make sure we extracted you safely?

100
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,151
And now you're lecturing me about trust?

101
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:54,236
Mikoy.

102
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:00,660
Fair enough.

103
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:02,536
We made a mistake.

104
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:05,831
We broke the safehouse rules.

105
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:09,585
You're quite the charmer.

106
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:13,005
Believe me.

107
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:15,674
Come on. It's Brusko.

108
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:16,842
You know,

109
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:20,554
we need to be three times,

110
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:22,807
or even ten times, more careful.

111
00:11:23,307 --> 00:11:26,060
Because La Morte Bianca
doesn't think like us.

112
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,145
Even I'm scared.

113
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:34,151
To be fair,
you've always been a scaredy-cat.

114
00:11:35,319 --> 00:11:36,404
True enough.

115
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,907
Alex, I'm sorry.

116
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:46,330
We're all truly grateful
for everything you've done.

117
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:48,582
It's just that

118
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,377
even if you and Chiara
don't always see eye to eye,

119
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,171
why not give her a chance?

120
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:57,633
As soon as she gets back,

121
00:11:57,716 --> 00:12:00,803
we'll do everything we can
to earn your trust again.

122
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:02,346
That's a promise!

123
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:06,600
There you go again.

124
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:08,727
Is that what love does to you?

125
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,021
You don't see the red flags?

126
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:12,773
You don't see the obvious?

127
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:16,318
But no.

128
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:18,654
We need a different strategy.

129
00:12:22,199 --> 00:12:23,617
But I already know that.

130
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:26,203
She raised me.

131
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,540
She trained me.

132
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:36,297
That's why I admire you so much.

133
00:12:40,217 --> 00:12:44,930
Alex, when you love someone,
you make room for trust.

134
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:47,641
That's how almost every relationship is.

135
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:51,562
Whether it's romantic, platonic,
or even family!

136
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,355
Trust is the foundation.

137
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:57,818
That's why I choose to trust Chiara.

138
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,862
That's how it should be.

139
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:06,911
Even after everything she kept from you?

140
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:09,330
Well, so did I.

141
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:11,999
I kept a lot of secrets from her too.

142
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,209
So we're even.

143
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:14,793
Right?

144
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:21,175
But how can you be sure
she's not hiding anything anymore?

145
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:28,057
We promised each other
we'd keep nothing hidden.

146
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:36,398
Besides, Chiara and I
only have one simple dream.

147
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,735
And we'll do whatever it takes
to make it come true.

148
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,029
We'll find a way.

149
00:13:48,118 --> 00:13:51,539
Within the hour,
the CCTV system will be reactivated.

150
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,043
We can't stay here long.

151
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:58,379
The head of security might get suspicious.

152
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:00,839
By the way, here's what we discussed.

153
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,972
And that way is to escape.

154
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:09,348
Is that it, Mikoy?

155
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,475
When Chiara said she wanted to run away,

156
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,602
you were just going to go along with it?

157
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:15,938
It's not like that.

158
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:19,233
Just like me, Chiara misses her family.

159
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:21,443
Think about it,
we spent months in Hong Kong

160
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:23,529
without any contact with our loved ones.

161
00:14:23,612 --> 00:14:24,989
That wasn't easy!

162
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:29,910
You know, even if she's
a strong, independent girl,

163
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,871
she's still family-oriented.

164
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:36,166
You need to take the long cut.

165
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:42,548
It's basically the same thing!

166
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:44,174
I've already studied it.

167
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,678
But personally, I haven't tried it yet.

168
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:50,180
You'll be the first.

169
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:53,726
Is it safe?

170
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:57,479
Completely safe from
La Morte Bianca's eyes.

171
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:01,025
If the elements are the same.

172
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:11,118
Like when it suddenly rains,
then the sun comes out.

173
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,746
You know, the usual suspects.

174
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:15,372
Right?

175
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:26,592
You know, I still can't help
worrying about her.

176
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:30,596
I mean, what if La Morte Bianca
is waiting for her?

177
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,556
Right? She's all alone.

178
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:12,179
Hey, handsome! Nice taho. It's green.

179
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:17,518
I bet if I drink that,
I'll turn into the Hulk.

180
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,020
Withdrawing.

181
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:22,398
Come on, that's not taho.

182
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:25,943
It's what all the kids
are into these days.

183
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:27,486
Matcha latte.

184
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:31,115
- That's right!
- Exactly!

185
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:33,617
This isn't matcha latte.

186
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:38,580
For building muscle!

187
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,500
You okay, buddy?

188
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:42,584
Yes.

189
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:45,212
Why are you so stiff? You're like a robot.

190
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:48,132
Hey. You three.

191
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:49,842
You know, this is all your fault,

192
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:51,593
why I turned like this.

193
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:30,174
Please forgive these troublemakers, but…

194
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:32,760
they mean well.

195
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,011
When we're asleep.

196
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:36,597
Stop teasing him.

197
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,432
A stiff neck is no joke!

198
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:42,352
Cocoy, I have an ointment for that.

199
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:44,146
I'll give it to you later.

200
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,064
I'll get it from my room.

201
00:17:45,147 --> 00:17:46,690
Really, Ms. Tess?

202
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:48,192
Thank you so much!

203
00:17:48,275 --> 00:17:50,736
And the three of you,
next time, you ask first

204
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,697
if someone's already using a bed.

205
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,324
- Yes, Mario.
- Yes, Mario.

206
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:58,160
Sorry too, buddy.

207
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:00,704
We're still adjusting.

208
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,711
That's okay.

209
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,547
I was the same when I first got here.

210
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:11,840
You'll adjust too.

211
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:14,635
Cocoy, weren't you scared?

212
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:16,220
There'll be no burglars.

213
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:17,513
What if there are ghosts?

214
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:26,939
There are no ghosts here!

215
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:29,525
Don't worry.

216
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:34,113
Any garlic?

217
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:38,283
I'll give this to Ms. Tess.

218
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:39,451
Here, Ms. Tess.

219
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,245
This will go great with fried rice.

220
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:42,788
Thank you.

221
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,751
How's your morning, Mikoy?

222
00:18:48,335 --> 00:18:51,421
I'm okay. Didn't get enough sleep,
but how about you?

223
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,465
We're doing okay too.

224
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:56,927
Were you two up late together last night?

225
00:18:58,387 --> 00:18:59,972
Together?

226
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:04,101
Cut it out.

227
00:19:04,726 --> 00:19:05,561
Or else…

228
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,648
We stayed up waiting for Chiara.
That's why we don't have enough sleep.

229
00:19:09,731 --> 00:19:12,568
Is it true Chiara went to see Viktor?

230
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:14,486
Yes, Mom.

231
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:17,156
Do you think…

232
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:20,826
she'll come back?

233
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,953
Of course, sir.

234
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:31,086
But if Chiara isn't back by midnight,
we'll regroup.

235
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,547
We need to make sure everyone is secure.

236
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:39,094
Can you please?

237
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:45,142
Come on, Agent Alex.

238
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:46,476
Mikoy.

239
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:49,104
We're just doing our job.

240
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:52,232
We have to make sure
everyone here is safe.

241
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:56,904
I'm sorry, everyone.

242
00:19:58,113 --> 00:20:01,200
I'm sure this wasn't the plot twist
you expected in your lives.

243
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:03,577
I'm only asking…

244
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:05,829
for a little more trust.

245
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:07,748
Just trust.

246
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:11,376
I'm sure my sweetheart
will be here any minute now.

247
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:14,546
That's enough!

248
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:18,008
- Hey.
- Son, we support you.

249
00:20:18,091 --> 00:20:19,259
That's right. Hey.

250
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,428
Let's just eat.

251
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,389
Food's ready!

252
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:26,642
- Can I join you?
- Come on, Coy!

253
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,101
- Nice!
- Let's go!

254
00:20:46,703 --> 00:20:47,829
Just what if…

255
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:50,415
What if Chiara needs help?

256
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,626
Could we extract her?

257
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:55,837
That's something
we can't guarantee, right?

258
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,131
Why not?

259
00:20:58,215 --> 00:21:00,175
You extracted my family.

260
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,511
Even our neighbors and friends.

261
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,721
Chiara should be included too, right?

262
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:10,185
If you and Chiara were together in Cebu,

263
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,728
it would've been easier.

264
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:14,356
But if she's in
La Morte Bianca's territory,

265
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:15,899
it would put our team at risk.

266
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:23,782
Even just a little help. Some support.

267
00:21:23,865 --> 00:21:25,909
Just so we can make sure Chiara is safe.

268
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:28,203
Maybe we won't even need an extraction.

269
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,247
Because you said earlier…

270
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:33,333
your sweetheart would be back soon.

271
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:11,496
Bok.

272
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:13,415
Are you okay?

273
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,836
Want me to take over? Go get some sleep.

274
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:19,963
I'm fine.

275
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:22,841
I won't be able to sleep anyway
until Chiara gets back.

276
00:22:25,969 --> 00:22:26,803
Bok.

277
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:30,432
I know that's everyone's
priority right now.

278
00:22:31,183 --> 00:22:32,559
But maybe you've forgotten

279
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:34,686
that we also have our own lives

280
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:37,522
that deserve a little attention too.

281
00:22:39,775 --> 00:22:40,609
Hey.

282
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:42,027
So what's the plan?

283
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:44,446
Plan for what?

284
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:45,655
Oh my God.

285
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:48,283
See?

286
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:52,996
You're so buried in work
that you even forgot your own birthday.

287
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,915
It's almost here, you know?

288
00:22:55,499 --> 00:23:01,129
Bok, you've only got
six days and 20 hours until your birthday!

289
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:02,881
Wow!

290
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:04,925
You sound more excited than I am.

291
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,176
Of course!

292
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:12,349
Not like that. What I'm saying is,

293
00:23:12,432 --> 00:23:16,561
all of us only get one birthday each year.

294
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:19,356
And on that day, it's the one day…

295
00:23:21,274 --> 00:23:26,488
when we can just enjoy ourselves,
relax, and be a little selfish.

296
00:23:27,447 --> 00:23:28,281
Don't you want that?

297
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:34,037
Seriously?

298
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:37,582
Do you really think I can take
a birthday leave right now?

299
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,794
For all I know, Chiara
may have gone back to the Moravianos.

300
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:46,675
I don't know. It's like the word
"selfish" isn't in your vocabulary.

301
00:23:47,342 --> 00:23:49,177
It's okay to be selfish sometimes.

302
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,721
Even if it's just for five minutes.

303
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:54,599
Just think about yourself for once.

304
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,434
I can't.

305
00:23:56,518 --> 00:24:00,272
There's a high chance
Chiara went back to the Moravianos.

306
00:24:00,355 --> 00:24:03,191
And if that's what happened,
what happens to us?

307
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:05,443
What if they come after us here?

308
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:13,994
What is that?!

309
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:36,683
<i>Why are you upset?</i>

310
00:24:36,766 --> 00:24:39,060
<i>Obviously because of that La Morte Bianca.</i>

311
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:40,645
<i>And Chiara.</i>

312
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:43,565
Because I miss our daughter, Viktor.

313
00:24:58,955 --> 00:25:01,041
<i>Mario, can we do this?</i>

314
00:25:01,124 --> 00:25:02,876
We have to. Just hang on.

315
00:25:02,959 --> 00:25:06,922
To ease your worries,
I have something to give you.

316
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:09,174
But take care of it, okay?

317
00:25:12,219 --> 00:25:14,304
<i>You have to understand.</i>

318
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:18,642
I will just use this to lessen my worries.

319
00:25:18,725 --> 00:25:21,269
<i>If that La Morte Bianca</i>

320
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:26,274
can explode our house and bakery,

321
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:31,196
then she can explode any place
and island here, right?
